description:
Rewrite both filter functions in internal/service/filter.go.

## filterDirect

New logic: include a PR when I am in reviewRequests as a User AND:
- at least one of my requests has `AsCodeOwner=false` (explicit), OR
- there are no other reviewers on the PR at all (sole reviewer)

```go
func filterDirect(prs []github.PullRequest, myLogin string) []github.PullRequest {
    for _, pr := range prs {
        isMine, meExplicit, hasOthers := false, false, false
        for _, rr := range pr.ReviewRequests.Nodes {
            if rr.RequestedReviewer.Type == "User" && rr.RequestedReviewer.Login == myLogin {
                isMine = true
                if !rr.AsCodeOwner { meExplicit = true }
            } else {
                hasOthers = true
            }
        }
        if isMine && (meExplicit || !hasOthers) { ... }
    }
}
```

- Remove the `teams *TeamService` parameter — no longer needed
- Remove the `SharesTeamWith` check entirely
- Update the `Filter` dispatcher call accordingly

## filterCodeowner

New logic: fallback — include a PR when it is NOT direct AND NOT team.

```go
func filterCodeowner(prs []github.PullRequest, myLogin string, teams *TeamService) []github.PullRequest {
    result := ...
    for _, pr := range prs {
        if !matchesDirect(pr, myLogin) && !matchesTeam(pr, myLogin, teams) {
            result = append(result, pr)
        }
    }
    return result
}
```

Extract `matchesDirect` and `matchesTeam` predicates (or inline) to avoid duplicating logic.

- Remove `classifyReviewRequests` and `allTrue` helpers (no longer used)
- Update function comments

## Acceptance Criteria
- filterDirect uses new predicate
- filterCodeowner is pure fallback
- classifyReviewRequests/allTrue removed
- make test passes (tests will need updating per inbox-ghq)
